## 🐛 Bug Report

When I try to set a specific cell fill using `worksheet.getCell('A2')`, the fill is applied to all cells in A column.
Lib version: 4.2.1

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
const Excel = require('exceljs');
const workbook = new Excel.Workbook();

(async () => {
  await workbook.xlsx.readFile(
    './exampleSpreadsheet.xlsx'
  );
  const ws = workbook.getWorksheet('example sheet');
  ws.getCell('A2').fill = {
    type: 'pattern',
    pattern: 'solid',
    fgColor: { argb: 'FFFFFF00' },
  };
  await workbook.xlsx.writeFile(
    'exampleSpreadsheet.xlsx'
  );
})();
```

## The expected behaviour:
A2 cell color is changed to argb FFFFFF00 (yellow)


## Actual behaviour:

All 'A' column cell colors are changed to argb FFFFFF00 (yellow)

comments.body:
try this
```
ws.getCell('A2').style = {
    ...ws.getCell('A2').style,
    fill: {
      type: 'pattern',
      pattern: 'solid',
      fgColor: { argb: 'FFFFFF00' },
     }
}
```
